<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="281" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1014,1225,1324]" box="[151,436,1297,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
Chinese name: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,436,1298,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">毛ffiẘoi</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1042,1366,1390]" box="[151,1042,1366,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1366,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Li" authorityName="Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,595,1366,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Argyresthiidae" genus="Socifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asymmetra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[294,496,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Socifera asymmetra</emphasis>
Liu &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[605,686,1366,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[605,686,1366,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, present designation by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1436,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
The association of the new genus with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruand" authorityYear="1850" box="[585,751,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Argyresthiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Argyresthiidae</taxonomicName>
is primarily based on the autapomorphies proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kyrki, J." pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="71 - 84" refId="ref4227" refString="Kyrki, J. (1984) The Yponomeutoidea: a reassessment of the superfamily and its suprageneric groups (Lepidoptera). Insect systematics &amp; evolution, 15 (1), 71 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631284 X 00064" type="journal article" year="1984">Kyrki (1984)</bibRefCitation>
: 1) vinculum with anterior protrusion of lateral angle (saccus), and 2) the V or Y-shaped eighth sternite in male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="282" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1436,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1544,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus is similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[765,895,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[765,895,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in external morphology. It can be distinguished from the latter in the male genitalia by the clavate socius bearing spine-like setae, the dense and long setae of the valva and the saccus much longer than the valva; while in 
<taxonomicName box="[829,959,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,959,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the flat socius is covered with scale-like setae, the valva is covered with sparse setae along margin (subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Moriuti" authorityYear="1969" box="[930,1044,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Argyresthiidae" genus="Blastotere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[930,1044,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Blastotere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or with a clump or a row of long and thick setae in disc, or with dense short setae (subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[830,960,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,960,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the saccus is shorter than the valva. In the female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[420,513,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Argyresthiidae" genus="Socifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[420,513,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Socifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[521,627,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[521,627,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a ductus seminalis originated from near the base of the ductus bursae, and has a smooth signum with smooth horns; while in 
<taxonomicName box="[815,945,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[815,945,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ductus seminalis is originated from the posterior 1/6 to anterior 1/3 of the ductus bursae, the signum and its horns are both denticulated, except smooth on horns of some individuals of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Heydenreich, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Heydenreich" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[482,1026,1832,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevigatella" subGenus="Blastotere">
<emphasis box="[482,499,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[523,637,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Blastotere</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[654,786,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">laevigatella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Heydenreich, G. H." box="[801,1018,1832,1859]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref4150" refString="Heydenreich, G. H. (1851) Lepidopterorum europaeorum catalogus methodicus. Systematisches Verzeichniss der Europaeischen Schmetterlinge. Dritte Ausgabe. Julius Klinkhardt, Leipzig, 131 pp." type="book" year="1851">Heydenreich, 1851</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1082,1099,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1123,1140,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1164,1284,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">sevenssoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bengtsson, B. A. &amp; Johansson, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="257 - 274" refId="ref3556" refString="Bengtsson, B. A. &amp; Johansson, R. (2011) Review of the unicolorous species of the subgenus Blastotere (Lepidoptera, Argyresthiidae) with descriptions of Argyresthia svenssoni sp. n. and A. kulfani sp. n. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 132 (4), 257 - 274. [http: // www. sef. nu / download / entomologisk _ tidskrift / et _ 2011 / ET 2011 % 20257 - 274 w. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2011">
Bengtsson 
<emphasis box="[1416,1436,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">et</emphasis>
Johansson, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1436,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1904,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Adult.</emphasis>
Medium size. Glossy. Occiput with piliform scales appressed, similar to several tropical species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1436,2044]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,255]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="282" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,305,1976,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Venation</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[321,387,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,899,923]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,280,870]" captionTargetId="figure-74@2.[155,1431,273,876]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Venation of S. asymmetra sp. nov., paratype, female, slide No. LTT12483W (Scale bar = 1.0 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6673480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6673480/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Forewing with Sc to middle of costa, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[853,861,1994,2008]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">1</subScript>
originated from middle of upper margin of cell, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1994,2008]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">2</subScript>
from before upper angle of cell, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[535,543,2030,2044]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">3</subScript>
from upper angle of cell, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[855,863,2030,2044]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">4</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[937,945,2030,2044]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">5</subScript>
separate; stem of M and accessory cell visible; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[234,242,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">2</subScript>
from near lower angle of cell, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[618,626,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[735,743,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">1</subScript>
connate and from lower angle of cell, CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1238,1246,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">2</subScript>
from near lower angle of cell; CuP visible distally; 1A + 2A with short basal fork. Hindwing with Rs to before apex, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1336,1344,205,219]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,205,219]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">2</subScript>
stalked, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[269,277,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[385,393,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">1</subScript>
stalked.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6673480" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6673480" box="[151,1280,899,924]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6673480/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" startId="2.[151,250,899,923]" targetBox="[162,1426,280,870]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1280,899,924]" box="[151,1280,899,924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,899,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. Venation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[405,541,899,923]" class="Insecta" family="Argyresthiidae" genus="Socifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asymmetra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[405,541,899,923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">S. asymmetra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,628,899,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[548,628,899,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, paratype, female, slide No. LTT12483W (Scale bar = 1.0 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,969,1320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,969,995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tuba analis stubby. Socius clavate, with piliform and spine-like setae, but without scale-like setae as in 
<taxonomicName box="[280,410,1005,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,410,1005,1031]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valva densely covered with strong and long setae. Vinculum heavily sclerotized. Saccus extremely long. Phallus slender, endophallus or vesica formed by cornuti with strong spines distally, ductus ejaculatorius extremely long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,969,1320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,1113,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Ductus bursae slender; ductus seminalis from near base of ductus bursae. Signum smooth, with horns separated from each other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,969,1320]" box="[199,1414,1185,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,457,1185,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Abdominal structure.</emphasis>
Second sternite with a pair of short sclerotized ridges at middle near anterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="282" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,969,1320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1221,1247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name is derived from the prefix “ 
<emphasis box="[872,917,1222,1247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">soci</emphasis>
-” of the Latin words “ 
<emphasis box="[1181,1251,1222,1247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">socius</emphasis>
”, and the suffix “- 
<emphasis box="[173,218,1257,1283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">fera</emphasis>
” meaning setae, indicating the socius with piliform and spine-like setae that are obviously different from the scale-like setae in 
<taxonomicName box="[357,487,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[357,487,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The generic name is interpreted as feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
